	     Cape Town – An almost seven-hour rescue operation saved the life of a paraglider near Porterville, in the Western Cape, on Tuesday. The paraglider had been hanging off the side of the mountain since 14:30 on Tuesday. He was rescued around 21:30, Wilderness Search and Rescue spokesperson Johann Marais said.  Paramedics and technical rescuers were taken to the scene. They put the man on a drip and stabilised him. An SAAF Oryx helicopter was used in the rescue. The man would be flown to Air Force Base Ysterplaat and taken to hospital via ambulance.    24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  